  "response_text": "A Febreze Air bottle stands upright on a grey kitchen counter, its white bottle decorated with pink flower imagery and a purple spray top. Behind it, softly out of focus, an adult woman in a light blue long-sleeve sweater reaches toward it. She picks up the bottle, and the view opens to a bright, modern white kitchen with pale blue accents, a large island, blue stools, white cabinets, a stainless-steel range hood, and daylight coming through a window. The woman, with long light-brown or blonde hair, moves energetically near the stove and sink area, holding the spray as if she is in the middle of freshening the room.\n\nTwo children sit or stand in the foreground with their backs partly to the kitchen. Then the view moves closer to them: a blonde girl in a pale blue cardigan and white top faces forward with a calm, slightly deadpan expression, while a younger blond boy with curly hair, wearing a blue striped shirt, leans in close to whisper into her ear. The girl keeps a straight face as he speaks, then the boy turns outward with a mischievous smile, and the girl’s expression softens into a small smile.\n\nBack in the kitchen, the adult woman raises the Febreze bottle high above her head and sweeps her other arm outward in a playful, dance-like pose. She smiles broadly, standing in front of the stainless-steel range and white cabinetry, with the spray bottle held up like a prop as she freshens the room.\n\nThe scene changes to a dimmer, more old-fashioned living room or sitting room with muted greenish lighting. An older woman with curly brown hair, light skin, and a patterned sweater vest over a long-sleeve blouse holds a green-and-white aerosol can. She lifts it and sprays a thick, cloudy mist across the room. The spray hangs visibly in the air as a dense fog, partially obscuring her face and the background furniture, which includes a framed picture, a shelf or cabinet, and a chair. She keeps her arm extended, continuing to spray, then lowers the can slightly and looks at it with a dissatisfied or skeptical expression.\n\nThe bright kitchen returns. The woman in the light blue sweater stands near the sink and window, holding the Febreze bottle out in front of her and spraying upward into the open space. A bowl of green apples sits on the island, and the white cabinets and pale blue backsplash make the room look clean and airy.\n\nA stylized demonstration follows: against a soft pastel background, translucent blue bubbles float among greenish, smoky-looking wisps. Small on-screen text near the bottom reads “Dramatization.” The green wisps appear to break apart or drift away as the blue bubbles move through the air, visually suggesting odor removal rather than simply covering the air with fog.\n\nThe woman appears again in the kitchen, now standing relaxed and smiling with the Febreze bottle held at her side. The room behind her is bright and tidy, with the island, blue stools, white cabinetry, and stainless-steel range visible.\n\nThe commercial ends on a clean light-blue background with product packaging displayed on the left: a tall pink Febreze Air Effects spray bottle and a green Febreze small-space-style freshener package. To the right, white text reads “Breathe Happy.” Across the lower half, a large white Febreze script logo stretches across the screen, decorated with small colorful hanging lights.",
